node.text: Fire lookouts in Washington are one of the best things about the mountains here. Getting able to sleep in a little house, with five star views, for free... just too good

clips_music_attribution_info.should_mute_audio_reason: Instagram music isn't available in your region.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by nathaniel wise in Cascade Mountains with @canonusa, and @ncascadesnps. May be an image of nature and sky.

node.text: Well, I’ve seen layers, but I haven’t seen layers and lightning. Until two nights ago. Shot in the dark, 30 second exposure at 100mm. The storm just missed us, thankfully. We were sleeping on a mountain top in a fire lookout, so, pretty exposed..

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by nathaniel wise in Tre Cime di Lavaredo. May be an image of nature and sky.

node.text: Insignificance. A candid shot of a man in Italy, one morning in the Dolomites. Love when the stars align for a moment like this one

node.text: A slightly blurry star photo from a very amateur star photographer. I’ve never taken the time to properly learn how to photograph the night sky, but in my few experiments, I’ve been inspired. Next time, I’ll use the 500 rule.. #neowisecomet #neowise

node.text: Hi. Just a photo of me, since I never post them. Hanging out in my happy place... golden hour, in a tent, in the mountains 📷- @christianschaffer

node.text: Moonrise a few nights ago. Love when it happens right at sundown. @autpops always posts moons on Monday, so I figure I’d give it a try.. happy #moonday

node.text: A break in the storm. From a wonderful four days spent car camping, sheltered from the weather in the rig, drinking coffee, reading, editing, staring at moody mountains, listening to rain hit the roof, feeling the wind shake my little home on wheels. Felt a bit more like a house boat that week, really..

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by nathaniel wise in Cascade Mountains. May be an image of nature and tree.

node.text: Autumn in the North Cascades. No matter what season it is, I always find myself dreaming of this one. It’s colder, but quieter, more colorful, and days in the mountains always seem dreamlike.  It’s my favorite time of year, no doubt. What’s yours?
